<subSubSection id="C33B656E252CFF83FF23E93576E9A340" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8B9E36E5252CFF83FF23E935771BA250" blockId="3.[151,1437,266,812]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">
The 
<taxonomicName id="4C214D66252CFF83FF7AE935746CA14F" box="[206,334,266,291]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nevadensis">
<emphasis id="B955EAF7252CFF83FF7AE935746CA14F" box="[206,334,266,291]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">nevadensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
subspecies that occurs at moderate to upper elevations in the Front Ranges of the Colorado Rocky Mountains is 
<taxonomicName id="4C214D66252CFF83FE2EE90D77EEA120" authority="Strecker, 1880" authorityName="Strecker" authorityYear="1880" box="[410,716,306,332]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="geneura">
<emphasis id="B955EAF7252CFF83FE2EE90D74D8A127" box="[410,506,306,331]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">geneura</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFB04B14252CFF83FDBAE90D77E1A120" author="Strecker" box="[526,707,306,332]" pageId="3" pageNumber="49" refString="Strecker, H. (1880) Descriptions of some species and varieties of North American Heteroceres, mostly new. Proceedings of the Davenport Academy of Science, 2, 270." type="journal article" year="1880">
Strecker, 
<number id="3DE924C2252CFF83FD30E90D77E1A120" box="[644,707,306,332]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" value="1880.0">1880</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Populations from Hinsdale County (
<number id="3DE924C2252CFF83FB2CE90D71FBA120" box="[1176,1241,306,332]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" value="9000.0">9000</number>
’ elevation) also appear to belong to this taxon. The name 
<taxonomicName id="4C214D66252CFF83FDC8E96577FEA11F" box="[636,732,346,371]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="geneura">
<emphasis id="B955EAF7252CFF83FDC8E96577FEA11F" box="[636,732,346,371]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">geneura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, previously associated with the larger, paler or brighter Arizona ­Texas taxon (
<figureCitation id="131A2A60252CFF83FE32E9BD74F5A1F0" box="[390,471,386,412]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,255,1047,1071]" captionTargetBox="[296,1291,397,1007]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[296,1292,397,1010]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Adult males of the Grammia nevadensis species group, a) G. n. nevadensis (Winnemuca, Humboldt Co., NV); b) G. n. superba (Victoria, Vancouver Is., BC); c) G. n. geneura (Estes Park, Larimer Co., CO); d) G. n. gibsoni (Burstall dunes, SK); e) G. behrii (Eight Dollar Mtn., Josephine Co., OR); f) G. i n c o r r u p t a (Comanche Natl. Grassland, Baca Co., CO); g) G. williamsii (Jenner, AB); h) G. eureka (HOLOTYPE, Eureka, Juab Co., UT); i) G. bowmani (PARATYPE, Black Ridge, Mesa Co., CO)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/175493/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">
Figs. 
<number id="3DE924C2252CFF83FE78E9BD74F5A1F0" box="[460,471,386,412]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
f, 
<number id="3DE924C2252CFF83FE43E9BD7725A1F0" box="[503,519,386,412]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" value="5.0">5</number>
), is not available in that sense because 
<taxonomicName id="4C214D66252CFF83FC5BE9BD716DA1F7" box="[1007,1103,386,411]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="geneura">
<emphasis id="B955EAF7252CFF83FC5BE9BD716DA1F7" box="[1007,1103,386,411]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">geneura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from Gilpin County, Colorado (
<number id="3DE924C2252CFF83FECCE995749EA1A8" box="[376,444,426,452]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" value="8500.0">8500</number>
’). This is outside the range and habitat of the southern taxon, and examination of the 
<typeStatus id="549A8847252CFF83FF23E9ED75DCA180" box="[151,254,466,492]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C214D66252CFF83FE90E9ED74A6A187" box="[292,388,466,491]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="geneura">
<emphasis id="B955EAF7252CFF83FE90E9ED74A6A187" box="[292,388,466,491]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">geneura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Field Museum of Natural history, Chicago, 
<collectingCountry id="F3367675252CFF83FC27E9ED7692A180" box="[915,944,466,492]" name="Iceland" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">IL</collectingCountry>
) confirms the true identity of this species. The species formerly associated with the name 
<taxonomicName id="4C214D66252CFF83FD65E9C57613A27F" box="[721,817,506,531]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="geneura">
<emphasis id="B955EAF7252CFF83FD65E9C57613A27F" box="[721,817,506,531]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">geneura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been revised to 
<taxonomicName id="4C214D66252CFF83FB9DE9C575FEA250" authority="Henry Edwards, 1881" authorityName="Henry Edwards" authorityYear="1881" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="incorrupta">
<emphasis id="B955EAF7252CFF83FB9DE9C571EAA27F" box="[1065,1224,506,531]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">G. incorrupta</emphasis>
(Henry Edwards, 
<number id="3DE924C2252CFF83FF23EA1D75F1A250" box="[151,211,546,572]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" value="1881.0">1881</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB04B14252CFF83FEB3EA1D7717A250" author="Ferguson" box="[263,565,546,572]" pageId="3" pageNumber="49" refString="Ferguson, D. C. &amp; Opler, P. A. (2006) Checklist of the Arctiidae (Lepidoptera: Insecta) of the continental United States and Canada. Zootaxa, 1299, 1 - 33." type="journal article" year="2006">
Ferguson &amp; Opler (
<number id="3DE924C2252CFF83FE58EA1D770FA250" box="[492,557,546,572]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" value="2006.0">2006</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9E36E5252CFF83FF72EA7576E9A340" blockId="3.[151,1437,266,812]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">
Males of 
<taxonomicName id="4C214D66252CFF83FE8CEA7574FAA20F" box="[312,472,586,611]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="incorrupta">
<emphasis id="B955EAF7252CFF83FE8CEA7574FAA20F" box="[312,472,586,611]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">G. incorrupta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C214D66252CFF83FCA8EA75769DA20F" box="[796,959,586,611]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nevadensis">
<emphasis id="B955EAF7252CFF83FCA8EA75769DA20F" box="[796,959,586,611]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">G. nevadensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the longer antennal pectinations, the longest averaging 
<quantity id="4CD99B00252CFF83FEDBEA4D74FAA2E0" box="[367,472,626,652]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.6" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" unit="mm" value="0.76">0.76 mm</quantity>
in 
<taxonomicName id="4C214D66252CFF83FE4AEA4D7759A2E7" box="[510,635,626,651]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="incorrupta">
<emphasis id="B955EAF7252CFF83FE4AEA4D7759A2E7" box="[510,635,626,651]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">incorrupta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
versus 
<quantity id="4CD99B00252CFF83FD63EA4D7662A2E0" box="[727,832,626,652]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.6" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" unit="mm" value="0.66">0.66 mm</quantity>
in 
<taxonomicName id="4C214D66252CFF83FCD2EA4D76C5A2E7" box="[870,999,626,651]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nevadensis">
<emphasis id="B955EAF7252CFF83FCD2EA4D76C5A2E7" box="[870,999,626,651]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">nevadensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; the dark­thorax phenotype common in 
<taxonomicName id="4C214D66252CFF83FF02EAA57455A2DF" box="[182,375,666,691]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="nevadensis" subSpecies="nevadensis">
<emphasis id="B955EAF7252CFF83FF02EAA57455A2DF" box="[182,375,666,691]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">G. n. nevadensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C214D66252CFF83FE00EAA57771A2DF" box="[436,595,666,691]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="nevadensis" subSpecies="superba">
<emphasis id="B955EAF7252CFF83FE00EAA57771A2DF" box="[436,595,666,691]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">G. n. superba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very rare in 
<emphasis id="B955EAF7252CFF83FCB8EAA57685A2DF" box="[780,935,666,691]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">G. i n c o r r u p t a</emphasis>
, and the entirely pale­buff thoracic collar (patagia) seen in about 
<number id="3DE924C2252CFF83FE04EAFD74ECA2B0" box="[432,462,706,732]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" value="25.0">25</number>
% of 
<taxonomicName id="4C214D66252CFF83FDA5EAFD77ACA2B7" box="[529,654,706,731]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="incorrupta">
<emphasis id="B955EAF7252CFF83FDA5EAFD77ACA2B7" box="[529,654,706,731]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">incorrupta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens never occurs in 
<taxonomicName id="4C214D66252CFF83FC6FEAFD715CA2B7" box="[987,1150,706,731]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nevadensis">
<emphasis id="B955EAF7252CFF83FC6FEAFD715CA2B7" box="[987,1150,706,731]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">G. nevadensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C214D66252CFF83FB3BEAFD700CA2B7" box="[1167,1326,706,731]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="incorrupta">
<emphasis id="B955EAF7252CFF83FB3BEAFD700CA2B7" box="[1167,1326,706,731]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">G. incorrupta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is multibrooded, while 
<taxonomicName id="4C214D66252CFF83FEF8EAD574CEA36F" box="[332,492,746,771]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nevadensis">
<emphasis id="B955EAF7252CFF83FEF8EAD574CEA36F" box="[332,492,746,771]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">G. nevadensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is univoltine, and females of 
<taxonomicName id="4C214D66252CFF83FCF0EAD576C3A36F" box="[836,993,746,771]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="incorrupta">
<emphasis id="B955EAF7252CFF83FCF0EAD576C3A36F" box="[836,993,746,771]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">G. incorrupta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are attracted to light while those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C214D66252CFF83FA37EAD5743AA347" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nevadensis">
<emphasis id="B955EAF7252CFF83FA37EAD5743AA347" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">G. nevadensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(and indeed of all other 
<emphasis id="B955EAF7252CFF83FD83EB2D77E3A347" box="[567,705,786,811]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">nevadensis­</emphasis>
group species) are not.
</paragraph>
